  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <p xml:id="Aink267-kilavi">talaimakaḷait talaimakaṉ varaival eṉat teḷittāṉ eṉṟ avaḷ kūṟak kēṭṭa tōḻi yavaṉ ciṟaippuṟattāṉākac colliyatu.
          </p>
        <p xml:lang="en">What the confidante said, as the hero was behind the hedge; [the confidante] who heard the heroine say that the hero had made it clear that he would marry her.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="Aink267">
<l>ciṟukaṭ paṉṟip peruñciṉa vorutta</l>
<l>ṟuṟuka laṭukkattu villōr māṟṟi</l>
<l>yaivaṉaṅ kavaruṅ kuṉṟa nāṭaṉ</l>
<l>vaṇṭupaṭu kūntalaip pēṇip</l>
<l>paṇpila collun tēṟutal cettē</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
        <l>The man from the land of the hills,</l>
        <l rend="space indent">where an incensed male boar with small eyes,</l>
        <l rend="indent">having diverted the archers</l>
        <l rend="indent">on the mountain slope with thick stones,</l>
        <l rend="indent">then seizes the wild rice—</l>
        <l rend="space">having cherished her tresses swarmed by bees,</l>
        <l>speaks things without substance,</l>
        <l>thinking [she would] believe [them].</l>
        
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
</text>
